    },
    {
      "text": "Rascal is a 1998 platform video game developed by Traveller's Tales and published by Psygnosis for the PlayStation. The main character and several enemies were designed by Jim Henson's Creature Shop.\nThe player takes control of a mischievous boy who travels through time to rescue his father, armed only with a \"Bubble Gun\". The game met with uniformly negative reviews which cited poor camera work and needlessly cumbersome controls.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "『バブルガンキッド』は1999年3月18日にタカラから、PlayStationにて発売されたアクションゲームで、イギリスのトラベラーズテイルズが1998年に開発したRascalの日本版。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "wikipedia_ja"
    },
    {
      "text": "Rascal, également connu sous le nom de Bubblegun Kid (バブルガンキッド) au Japon, est un jeu vidéo de plates-formes développé par Traveller's Tales et édité par Psygnosis (Takara au Japon), commercialisé en Europe en mars 1998, en Amérique du Nord le 31 mars 1998, et au Japon le 19 mars 1999 sur console PlayStation. Le personnage principal et divers ennemis du jeu ont été réalisés chez Jim Henson's Creature Shop.",
      "lang": "fr",
      "source": "wikipedia_fr"
    },
    {
      "text": "Rascal é um jogo de plataforma desenvolvido pela Traveller's Tales e publicado pela Psygnosis exclusivamente para o PlayStation. O personagem principal e vários inimigos foram desenhados pela loja de Criaturas de Jim Henson .",
      "lang": "pt",
      "source": "wikipedia_pt"
    }
  ]
